Multiple Counterparts 24 EXHIBITS: Exhibit A: Description of Shared Facilities Exhibit B: Description of Land Rights Documents Exhibit C: Owners Committee Exhibit D: Memorandum of Agreement SHARED FACILITIES COMMON OWNERSHIP AGREEMENT (Fiddler Solar Projects) This SHARED FACILITIES COMMON OWNERSHIP AGREEMENT ("Agreement"), dated as of July 6, 2015 (the "Effective Date"), is entered into by and among SunE Solar XVII Project1, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Fiddler 1"), SunE Solar XVII Project2, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Fiddler 2")and SunE Solar XVII Project3, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Fiddler 3"). Fiddler 1, Fiddle 2 and Fiddler 3 are each herein referred to as a "Party" and collectively as the "Parties". RECITALS A. Fiddler 1 is developing, and currently expects to construct, own and operate, a solar power electric generating facility to be located in Iron County, Utah having an installed nameplate capacity of three (3) MW AC ("Fiddler 1 Project"). B. Fiddler 2 is developing, and currently expects to construct, own and operate, a solar power electric generating facility to be located in Iron County, Utah having an installed nameplate capacity of three (3) MW AC ("Fiddler 2 Project"). C. Fiddler 3 is developing, and currently expects to construct, own and operate, a solar power electric generating facility to be located in Iron County, Utah having an installed nameplate capacity of three (3) MW AC ("Fiddler 3 Project"). The Fiddler 1 Project, the Fiddler 2 Project and the Fiddler 3 Project are each herein referred to as a "Project" and collectively as the "Projects". D. Each Project will be located on sites located in the general vicinity of each of the other Projects and each Project will be interconnected to the Transmission Owner's transmission system at the Interconnection Point (as defined herein) pursuant to the Interconnection Agreements (as defined herein). E. Fiddler 1 and Fiddler 2 each have an interest in jointly acquiring and owning as tenants-in-common certain easements for generation-tie power line purposes to be used to transmit energy produced by the Fiddler 1 Project and the Fiddler 2 Project to the point of interconnection (as more particularly described here, the "Shared Easement"), constructing, owning as tenant-in-common, using, operating and maintaining the generation-tie power line to be constructed on the Shared Easement (as more particularly described herein, the "Shared Line"). Likewise, Fiddler 1, Fiddler 2 and Fiddler 3 each have an interest in jointly acquiring leasehold interests in an extension of such Shared Easement easements for generation-tie power line purposes to be used to transmit energy produced by the Fiddler 1 Project, the Fiddler 2 Project and the Fiddler 3 Project to the point of interconnection (as more particularly described here, the "Three Party Easement"), constructing, owning as tenant-in-common, using, operating and maintaining the extension of such Shared Line. In addition, Fiddler 1, Fiddler 2 and Fiddler 3 each have an interest in jointly acquiring and owning as tenants in common and constructing, owning, using, operating and maintaining the Common Interconnection Facilities (as defined herein). F. The purpose of this Agreement is to document the agreement of the Fiddler 1 and Fiddler 2 as to their individual and common ownership rights, obligations, and use with respect to the Shared Easement and the Shared Line, and to document the agreement of Fiddler 1, Fiddler 2 and Fiddler 3 as to their individual and common ownership rights, obligations and use of Three Party Easement and the Common Interconnection Facilities. The term (the "Term") of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and continue in effect for so long as any of the Land Rights Documents remain in effect, plus any time required for disposing of such Shared Facilities as provided in Section 14.4, unless terminated earlier by mutual agreement of the Owners. INITIAL DEVELOPMENT of shared facilities 2.1 Design for Shared Facilities and Construction Schedule. The Owners have heretofore caused to be prepared the conceptual design for the Shared Line and the Common Interconnection Facilities (the "Design"). The Owners shall cooperate with one another to develop and implement a schedule for the procurement of the necessary equipment and materials and the construction and installation of the Shared Facilities so as to have the same completed on or before July 15, 2015. 2.2 Construction Budget. The Operator will solicit bids and recommend to the other Owners for their concurrence a construction contractor for the Shared Facilities utilizing the Design, and shall recommend to the other Owners for their concurrence a definitive budget (the "Construction Budget") for the estimated cost of designing and constructing the Shared Facilities, which Construction Budget shall separately break out the estimated cost of designing and constructing the Shared Line and the estimated cost of designing and constructing the Common Interconnection Facilities. The other Owner's concurrence in the selected contractor and the Construction Budget shall not be unreasonably withheld and shall be deemed granted if and to the extent the neither of the other Owners has objected to the recommendations by the Operator within ten (10) days after the Operator provides the other Owners with notice of such recommendations. Each of the other Owners concurs in advance to any Construction Budget providing for a total cost of constructing the Shared Facilities of no greater than six hundred and fifty six thousand dollars ($656,000). The Operator shall have the authority to approve change orders with respect to the construction of the Shared Facilities so long as: (a) the aggregate additional costs (i.e., costs that, when added to all other costs incurred or reasonably expected to incurred, exceed the costs covered by the Construction Budget) do not exceed ten percent (10%) of the aggregate amount of the Construction Budget, or (b) to the extent the cost of such change orders exceeds the amount specified in (a) above, such change order is approved by at least two (2) of the Owners (one of which may be the Operator) acting through the Operating Committee. The costs incurred pursuant to any change order approved as required in this Section 2.3 shall be deemed to be a part of the Construction Budget for all purposes of this Agreement. 2.3 Operator Construction Authority. The Operator shall arrange for the construction of the Shared Facilities in accordance with this Agreement. The Operator shall have the exclusive right to manage the construction of the Shared Facilities. After commencing the construction of the Shared Facilities, the Operator shall work in good faith to cause the Shared Facilities to be completed expeditiously and in accordance with the Construction Budget and otherwise in accordance with the terms of the Land Rights Documents and all applicable laws, including applicable permits and licenses. OWNERSHIP and use of SHARED facilities Ownership and Use of Shared Facilities. Ownership Interests. The Parties shall hold ownership interests (each an "Ownership Interest") in the Shared Facilities as follows: Fiddler 1 and Fiddler 2 shall each have an undivided fifty percent (50%) Ownership Interest as tenants in common in the Shared Easement and that portion of the Shared Line that runs over the Shared Easement; and Fiddler 1, Fiddler 2 and Fiddler 3 shall each have an undivided one-third (1/3) Ownership Interest in the Common Interconnection Facilities as tenants in common, it being acknowledged and agreed that Fiddler 3 shall retain its underlying leasehold interest it has in the Three Party Easement (to be occupied and used concurrently with the occupancy and use thereof by Fiddler 1 and Fiddler 2 pursuant to their subleasehold interest described in item (6)(a) in Exhibit B hereto) under the Land Rights Documents described in item (6)(b) in Exhibit B hereto, and Fiddler 1 and Fiddler 2 shall each have an Ownership Interest consisting of an undivided one-half (1/2) interest in the Sublease Agreement described in item (6)(a) in Exhibit B hereto. Undivided Use Interests. Fiddler 1 and Fiddler 2 shall each have an undivided right to the use or capacity of the Shared Easement and the portion of the Shared Line located within the Shared Easement equal to its respective Proportionate Share therein, and each Owner shall have an undivided right to the use or capacity of the of that portion of the Shared Line located within the Three Party Easement equal to its respective Proportionate Share and an undivided right to the use of capacity of the Common Interconnection Facilities equal to its respective Proportionate Share therein (such undivided rights being herein called the "Undivided Use Interest"). Transmission Capacity. Each Owner shall be entitled to use its Undivided Use Interest in the Delivery Capability of the Shared Facilities. In the event of a partial curtailment of Delivery Capability by Transmission Owner or a de-rating of the Shared Facilities, each Owner's Undivided Use Interest will be reduced pro rata in accordance with its Proportionate Share of the affected Shared Facilities for the duration of the curtailment or de-rating. In the event that the Delivery Capability of the Shared Facilities exceeds the capability provided in the applicable Interconnection Agreement, with Transmission Owner's and Transmission Owner's consent and approval, each Owner's Undivided Use Interest will be increased pro rata in accordance with its Proportionate Share for so long as the Delivery Capability is in excess of the capability provided in the Interconnection Agreements with Transmission Owner's and Transmission Owner's consent and approval. Access . Each Owner shall have a non-exclusive right of access to the Shared Facilities as necessary in order to ensure that Operator is meeting its obligations with respect to operation, maintenance and repair of such Shared Facilities, that such Owner's Project remains operational, and for all other purposes contemplated by this Agreement. In accessing the Shared Facilities, an Owner shall not unreasonably interfere with Operator's operation, maintenance or repair of the Shared Facilities or of another Owner's Project. No Owner shall have access to another Owner's mechanical, structural and electrical/telecommunication components or equipment, or real property, that is not part of the Shared Facilities. Statement of Intent. The ownership structure set forth in this Section 3.1 is not organized with the intention or expectation of producing revenue or making a profit from the operation of the Shared Facilities but merely as an ownership form through which the Owners can accomplish their purpose of owning, operating and making the Shared Facilities available for the use of the Owners in connection with their respective, separate Projects. Nothing in this Agreement is intended or shall be construed to create any partnership, joint venture or similar relationship among the Owners; and in no event shall any Owner take a position on any tax return or other writing of any kind that a partnership, joint venture or other similar relationship exists. The Owners do not intend to form or hold themselves out as a de jure or de facto partnership, joint venture or similar relationship, to share profits or losses, or to share any joint control over financial decisions or discretionary actions (other than as may be provided in the Land Rights Documents). At no time shall the Shared Facilities be used by any person other than an Owner, except as otherwise may be required by Law or the Interconnection Agreements. Subject to the rights of each Owner under Article 9 (in the event of the possible sale or other disposition of its Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities) or under Section 14.4 (in the event all or a portion of the Shared Facilities is or are removed from service), the Owners do not expect to receive any material amount of revenue from the Shared Facilities. In the event a third party has a right under applicable Law to utilize all or any portion of the Shared Facilities and seeks to do so, the Owners will cooperate with each other to provide such third party access to the Shared Facilities in accordance with the requirements of Law, and to the full extent permitted under Law, the third party seeking to so utilize all or any portion of the Shared Facilities shall be required to pay all costs and expenses incurred by the Owners in connection therewith. Interconnection of Projects. Each of the Owners and their respective successors and assigns shall have the right, at their respective sole cost and expense, to interconnect their Projects and to deliver electrical energy generated by such Projects via the Shared Facilities pursuant to and in accordance with the terms and provisions set forth herein. The Owners shall cooperate in good faith to accomplish the interconnection of the Projects so as to minimize, to the extent reasonably practicable, the interruption and reduction of deliveries from the Projects of the other Owners. Use of Shared Facilities Land Rights and Shared Facilities. Except to the extent otherwise agreed in writing by the Owners Committee, each Party shall use the Shared Facilities Land Rights solely to install, maintain and operate the Shared Facilities. Except to the extent otherwise agreed in writing by the Owners Committee, each Party shall use the Shared Facilities solely for the purpose of installing, maintaining and operating its Project. Each Owner shall be solely responsible for installing, operating, and maintaining its Project and for paying all costs required to be paid by it under the Interconnection Agreement pertaining to its Project, in each case at the sole cost of the Owner of such Project; provided that in so installing, operating, and maintaining such Project, each Owner shall: (i) generally cooperate with the other Owners in terms of making all reasonable efforts to coordinate the scheduling of installation, maintenance and other activities related to its Project at mutually agreeable times, and, provide at least thirty (30) days prior written notice to the other Owners of commencement of any planned maintenance or repair activities related to its Project together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, and for unplanned maintenance or repair activities related to its Project, provide notice to the other Owners promptly upon discovery of the need for such activities; (ii) comply with any written safety and operating requirements of the Operator when accessing and performing work that may impact the Shared Facilities; (iii) otherwise make all reasonable efforts to conduct such activities so as to minimize, to the extent reasonably possible, any interference with each other Owner's use of its Project or the Shared Facilities; (iv) if and to the extent reasonably possible, schedule during an off-peak and/or low solar generation time period any required disconnection of each other Owners' Projects related to such Owner's installation, maintenance and repairs of its Project in order to minimize the impact on any other Owner; and (v) indemnify and hold harmless each other Owner from all claims and property damage incurred or suffered as a result of its installation, maintenance or repair activities related to its Project. Each Party shall compensate each other Party for any reasonable, documented losses, costs, damages and expenses due to any forced outages, scheduled outages or other interruption or reduction of deliveries of electrical power from the other Owners' Projects caused by such Owner's use of the Shared Facilities to install, operate and maintain such Owner's Project. Further Assurances. Each Owner shall promptly take such action (including the execution and delivery bills of sale and other reasonable and customary documents and instruments consistent with this Agreement) as may reasonably be requested by any other Owner to effect, evidence or vest each Owner's respective Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities, or to evidence the transfer by such other Owner of any of its Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities. Rights Subject to Land Rights Documents. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, all of the rights of the Parties under this Agreement are subject to the terms and conditions of the Land Rights Documents. This Agreement does not grant to any Owner any rights, interests or benefits greater than those provided to or permitted under the Land Rights Documents; and this Agreement are limited by and taken subject to the terms, conditions and provisions of the Land Rights Documents. OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES Construction of Shared Facilities. Each Owner shall pay its Proportionate Share of all construction costs of the Shared Facilities as set forth herein. Operation and Maintenance of Shared Facilities. Subject to the Owners reimbursing Operator for the applicable costs related thereto, during the term of this Agreement, the Operator shall exercise commercially reasonable efforts to operate and maintain (or provide for the operation and maintenance of) the Shared Facilities in accordance with this Agreement. SHARED FACILITIES management Appointment, Resignation and Removal of Operator; Shared Facilities Actions to Be Taken by Operator. Appointment of Initial Operator. Fiddler 1 is hereby appointed to be the initial Operator, subject to Fiddler 1's right to resign as Operator. The Owners hereby engage the Operator to manage, operate, maintain and repair the Shared Facilities and to perform other duties pertaining to the Shared Facilities (the "OandM Services"), all as set forth in this Agreement. Fiddler 1 hereby accepts such engagement and agrees to perform such duties in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. Removal and Resignation of Operator; Successor Operator. Any Owner may be removed as Operator upon the affirmative vote of the other two Owners acting through the Operating Committee. Any Owner may resign from acting as Operator by giving written notice to the other Owners. Upon any such removal or resignation of an Operator, the Owners, by majority vote of the Operating Committee, shall appoint another Person (who may, but need not, be an Owner) to act as Operator. Notwithstanding the foregoing or anything else expressed or implied herein to the contrary, no resignation or removal of an Operator shall be effective until another Person has been so appointed by the Operating Committee to act as Operator and such appointed Person has accepted such appointment in a writing delivered to the Owners. Shared Facilities Actions to Be Taken by Operator. All actions or activities an Owner has the right or obligation to take or perform on or with respect to the Shared Facilities shall be taken or performed by Operator. An Owner and its invitees shall have the right to inspect the Shared Facilities, provided however, that such inspection shall not unreasonably interfere with the repair, management, operations and maintenance of the Shared Facilities, and any Persons inspecting the Shared Facilities shall abide by any and all safety rules and procedures established by Operator that are not inconsistent with this Agreement or otherwise applicable to the Project, as communicated by the Operator prior to their access to the Shared Facilities; and provided further Operator may require that such Owner and its invitees be accompanied by Operator. Other Provisions Relating to Operator. Duties and Authority of Operator. In addition to the duties and authority set forth elsewhere in this Agreement, the Operator shall perform the following, and is hereby authorized to do the following, on behalf of each of the Owners: Manage the construction of the Shared Facilities in accordance with any the Interconnection Agreements, Good Utility Practice, applicable Laws, and this Agreement. Operate and maintain (or provide and contract with a third party for the operation and maintenance of) the Shared Facilities in accordance with the Interconnection Agreements, Good Utility Practice, applicable Laws, and this Agreement. In addition, the Operator shall effectuate such maintenance and repairs to the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably required by the Transmission Owner pursuant to any of the Interconnection Agreements for which the Operator receives written notice from the related Owner, in accordance with Good Utility Practice, to ensure that the Shared Facilities are compatible with the technical specifications, operational control and safety requirements of the Transmission Owner. In connection with such operation and maintenance, the Operator is authorized to interrupt service on the Shared Facilities by disconnecting all or any portions of the Projects and to require curtailments of Shared Facilities usage, in accordance with Good Utility Practice and in compliance with the terms of this Agreement. When so instructed by the Owner's Committee after the end of the use of the Shared Facilities, remove and dispose of the Shared Facilities and restore the site on which the Shared Facilities are located, in accordance with the Land Rights Documents and applicable laws and regulations (or provide and contract with a third party for such removal and restoration). Prepare annual budgets and budget amendments as required with respect to the Shared Facilities, and present such budgets and budget amendments for review and approval by the Owners Committee. Maintain books and records related to the Shared Facilities in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles and all applicable requirements of Law, if any, and make such books and records available to any Owner upon the request of such Owner during the Operator's regular business hours. Procure policies of insurance pursuant to Section 8.1; Take all actions as are required to maintain the Shared Facilities Land Rights to the extent within the Operator's reasonable ability to do so. Perform, in accordance with Good Utility Practice, such other duties as may be specified by the Owners Committee. Execute such contracts and other documents and expend monies necessary for the management, operation, maintenance and repair of the Shared Facilities or as are necessary or appropriate to carry out the duties enumerated in Agreement. Oversee all investigations, studies, clean up, corrective action or response or remedial action required by any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to the use, operation or ownership of the Shared Facilities. Upon the request of any Owner, promptly provide to such Owner a statement, in such detail as may be reasonably requested by such Owner, of the amounts payable or reimbursable by such Owner pursuant to Section 5.4. Standards for Operator's Performance; Risk of Loss. Operator shall perform the OandM Services in accordance with Good Utility Practice, the Interconnection Agreements, the Land Rights Documents, this Agreement and all other agreements relating to ownership, construction, operation and maintenance of the Shared Facilities, applicable Laws and requirements of Governmental Authorities, including without limitation all Hazardous Materials Laws and all Environmental Laws, and all safety policies and procedures. As between the Owners and the Operator, the Owners shall be responsible for the risk of loss to the Shared Facilities or any portion thereof during the repair, management, operation and maintenance of the Shared Facilities, regardless of cause, except to the extent such loss is caused in whole or in part by the gross negligence or willful misconduct of the Operator. Scheduled Maintenance. Operator shall schedule maintenance and any planned outages of the Shared Facilities so as to minimize interference with Owners' scheduled energy deliveries. Maintenance and any planned outages of the Shared Facilities shall be scheduled, to the maximum extent possible, during scheduled maintenance outages of the Owners' Facilities and during hours of low insolation. Each Owner will provide to the Operator and the other Owners by January I of each year a schedule of planned maintenance outages on such Owner's Project for the subsequent twelve-month period. Scheduled outages of the Shared Facilities will be subject to the mutual approval of the affected Owners, such approval not to be unreasonably withheld. Operator will seek to limit the duration of any outage, planned or unplanned, consistent with Good Utility Practice. Unplanned Outages. Operator will notify Owners of all emergency or unplanned outages of any of the Shared Facilities as soon as practicable, in accordance with Good Utility Practice, and will provide an estimated time of return of the Shared Facilities to service, or if not known, will keep Owners advised regarding the status of same, Emergency Conditions. In the event of an Emergency Condition involving the Shared Facilities that could be reasonably expected by Operator to result in possible personal injury, loss of life, damage to or destruction of property, or danger to the public, the Operator shall, without the need for prior notification of the Owners, take such action as may be reasonable and necessary, as determined in the sole discretion of the Operator, to prevent, avoid or mitigate such loss, and shall, as soon as reasonably practicable, report any such emergency, including the Operator's response thereto, to the Owners, and Operator shall be compensated by the Owners for the costs of taking such actions in proportion to their Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities so affected. Extraordinary Maintenance. Each Owner agrees to reimburse Operator for its Proportionate Share of the costs of any maintenance or other services required in the event of unusual or catastrophic circumstances, to the extent such costs were not included in the forecast budget for OandM Services ("Extraordinary Maintenance"). In such event, Operator will prepare a forecast budget for such Extraordinary Maintenance for Owners' review and performance of the Extraordinary Maintenance will be subject to Owners' prior approval, not to be unreasonably withheld, unless immediate action is required due to an Emergency Condition pursuant to Section 6.8. OandM Costs. Costs of performing OandM Services, including the costs of any Extraordinary Maintenance incurred by Operator (collectively, the "OandM Costs") shall include all payments made and expenses incurred by Operator in performing OandM Services (at cost and without markup), including but not limited to related overheads and applicable taxes, and costs (except insurance costs) related to ownership of the Shared Facilities. Each Owner shall be responsible for its Proportionate Share of OandM Costs, including its Proportionate Share of the costs of any Extraordinary Maintenance incurred by Operator. Consent or Approval Under Land Rights Documents. Operator shall not waive any provision of any Land Rights Document or grant any consent or approval of the Owners required pursuant to the Land Rights Documents without the prior written consent of the Owners, which shall not be unreasonably withheld or delayed. Authorized Expenditures. With respect to expenditures: (a) included in an annual budget or a budget amendment, in either case approved and effective pursuant to Section 6.7 of this Agreement, (b) included in the Construction Budget approved or deemed approved pursuant to Section 2.2 or included in an Operating Budget approved or deemed approved pursuant to Section 6.7, and (c) any additional expenditures properly incurred by the Operator with respect to the Shared Facilities or Shared Facilities Land Rights, each of the Owners shall reimburse to the Operator such Owner's Proportionate Share of such expenditures as provided in this Agreement. Such reimbursable costs shall include (i) the salaries, wages and related indirect and overhead costs properly allocable to the Shared Facilities for the Operator's personnel who perform the duties and obligations of the Operator pursuant to this Agreement and (ii) the payments by the Operator to third parties related to or in connection with the carrying out of the duties and obligations of the Operator pursuant to this Agreement. Reimbursement of Approved Costs. The invoicing and payment of any reimbursement pursuant to Section 5.3 shall be as follows: Funds to pay for amounts expended pursuant to Section 5.3 shall be advanced by the Owners at the beginning of each calendar month. Not later than ten (10) Business Days prior to the start of each calendar month (or such other billing period as is agreed by the Owners), the Operator shall deliver to each Owner a statement showing the computation in reasonable detail of the amount to be advanced to the account to pay for such expenditures, which shall be based on budgeted figures for the coming month adjusted for any surplus funds or funding inadequacies carried over from the latest completed month. Each Owner shall pay to the Operator any amount set forth in such statement within ten (10) Business Days (provided that such payment shall not be deemed a waiver of such Owners right to dispute any such amount as set forth below). Such payment shall be made by each Owner to the Operator in immediately available funds by electronic wire transfer, or by deposit otherwise made into the account designated in writing from time to time by the Operator for such purpose. The Operator shall promptly provide to each Owner such receipts, documents and other information in connection with each such statement as such Owner may reasonably request to the extent in the Operator's possession or reasonable control. Any dispute concerning a statement shall be subject to the dispute resolution process set forth in Section 11.1. Notwithstanding the provisions of Section 5.4(a) above, the Operator shall make available during regular business hours, for inspection and audit by each of the Owners, all books and records of the Operator evidencing the amounts contained in each statement provided to such Owner pursuant to Section 5.4(a). The books and records relevant to each statement shall be retained by the Operator for no less than two calendar years after the delivery date of the applicable statement, but not less than the period provided for by the FERC regulations applicable to Operator or with respect to the Shared Facilities regarding maintenance of books and records, if any; and such books and records shall be made available by the Operator for inspection and audit by each of the Owners during the Operator's regular business hours at the Operator's office. The costs and expenses of any inspection or audit requested by an Owner shall be borne by the Owner requesting such inspection or audit. Each Owner shall have the right to conduct such audits with respect to any statement for up to two (2) years following receipt of such statement. The Operator also shall permit any Owner to inspect the Shared Facilities during regular business hours, provided that such Owner arranges such inspection with the Operator and complies with the safety requirements imposed by the Operator. Owners Committee Establishment of Committee; Voting. There is hereby established an Owners Committee to oversee the management of the Shared Facilities, the Land Rights Documents and the Operator's day-to-day management of the foregoing in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, and to take all other actions that all of the Owners may, from time to time, agree in writing that the Owners Committee is authorized to take in connection with the ownership (as applicable). Each Owner shall be entitled to appoint one (1) member to the Owners Committee. Each member of the Owners Committee shall have the right to cast one (1) vote with respect to any decision, approval or other action to be made by the Owners Committee pursuant to this Agreement. Appointment of Members; Alternates. The members of the Owners Committee, as well as alternate members who may represent their respective Owners in the absence of the regular member, are identified on Exhibit C to this Agreement. Any Owner (or its successors and assigns, acting collectively) may change its Owners Committee member by giving written notice of such change to each other Owner, and upon receipt of such notice the Owners shall revise Exhibit C to this Agreement accordingly. Any Owner (or its successors and assigns, acting collectively), by giving written notice to each other Owner, may, for purposes of any decision, approval or other action to be made by the Owners Committee pursuant to this Agreement, appoint an alternate or alternates to serve on the Owners Committee in the place of, and to cast the vote of, the regular Owners Committee member appointed by such Owner. Meetings. The Owners Committee shall meet regularly, but not less often than once each year, at such time and place as may be agreed upon by the members of the Owners Committee, and the Owners Committee shall meet at such other reasonable times and places as may be requested by any Owners Committee member by written notice given in accordance with Section 13 to each other Owners Committee member at least thirty (30) days prior to such meeting; provided that if an Owners Committee member cannot participate at any proposed time or place set forth in any such notice, it shall notify the other Owners Committee member of its unavailability at the proposed time and place within ten (10) Business Days thereafter and provide in such notice a proposed alternate time or times when the notifying Owners Committee member would be available within thirty (30) days after the originally proposed time. The respective members then shall agree upon a mutually acceptable alternative time and place for a meeting, which time shall not be later than thirty (30) days after the originally proposed time. Members of the Owners Committee may participate in such meetings in person or by means of conference telephone calls or similar communications during which all persons participating in the meeting can hear each other. Participation in a meeting by means of conference telephone calls or similar communications shall be deemed to constitute presence in person at the meeting. Failure by any Owners Committee member to attend any annual or special meeting of the Owners Committee for which notice was properly given under this Section 6.3 (and for which no notice of unavailability was delivered) shall not invalidate such meeting or any decisions, approvals or other actions taken at such meeting by the sole attending Owners Committee member (provided that member holds the right to vote) in good faith, in a manner such member reasonably believes to be in the best interests of the Owners, and the single member attending such meeting (and holding a right to vote) shall be deemed to constitute a quorum. Decisions by Written Action. Any decisions, approvals and other actions that may be taken at a meeting of the Owners Committee may be taken without a meeting if all Owners Committee members consent thereto in writing (including, without limitation, writings by email). The Owners Committee may, by the unanimous vote of the members of the Owners Committee then holding a right to vote, adopt written procedures for review or approval of matters or for the taking of other actions concerning the Shared Facilities. Subcommittees. The Owners Committee may appoint such subcommittees as it deems necessary or appropriate and, by the unanimous vote of all of the members of the Owners Committee then having a right to vote, may delegate approval authority to such subcommittees with respect to matters concerning the Shared Facilities. Members of a subcommittee are not required to otherwise be a member of the Owners Committee. Decisions by Majority Vote. Except as otherwise expressly provided herein, decisions, approvals and other actions of the Owners Committee shall require the approval of a majority of the members of the Owners Committee. Operating Budgets. The Owners Committee shall have the authority to review and approve or amend the annual operating budgets and budget amendments prepared by the Operator pursuant to Section 5.2(a)(iii) (each annual budget and amendment thereto approved by the Operating Committee being herein referred to as an "Operating Budget"). If for any reason the Owners Committee does not approve an annual budget prior to the end of the eleventh (11th) month of the preceding operating year, the budget for such preceding operating year shall apply to operating year, subject to an increase or decrease in such budget to reflect the change in the GDPIPD for all goods and services during the twelve- (12) month period ending with the tenth (10th) month of such preceding operating year. The Owners Committee shall have the authority to amend or replace any Operating Budget. Emergency Actions. The Operator shall have the right but not the duty to proceed with an item that has been disapproved as provided in this Article 6, if the Operator determines in its reasonable judgment that such action is required to avoid an imminent threat of loss of life or property, is required to avoid an imminent threat of interruption of service over the Shared Facilities, or is required to avoid a non-compliance with Law or applicable contract requirements; provided, however, that if the Operator takes such action on a disapproved item and if the determination made in any subsequent review of the decision is that the item was not consistent with Good Utility Practice, then the Operator shall not be entitled to reimbursement for any of the cost or expense of such action and shall be liable to the other Owner(s) for any damages to such Owner(s) resulting from such disapproved action. Tax Election. Each of the Owners shall, to the extent permitted by Section 761 of the Code, elect as provided in Treasury Regulation Section 1.761-2 to exclude from the provisions of Subchapter K of the Code any organization that it may otherwise comprise by virtue of this Agreement. ADDITIONAL RIGHTS, COVENANTS AND OBLIGATIONS Land Rights Documents. Each Owner shall perform its obligations under each of the Land Rights Documents in all material respects and comply with all material terms and conditions applicable to the Land Right Documents. Notwithstanding any provision of the Land Rights Documents that would allow any Owner to quitclaim or surrender the same or any portion thereof, each shall keep and maintain each Land Rights Document in full force and effect for the full term thereof unless otherwise agreed in writing by all of the Owners. No Owner shall modify or amend, or consent to the modification or amendment, of any Land Right Documents in any manner that would currently or prospectively, interfere with the construction, installation, maintenance, or operation of the Shared Facilities or a Project with the prior written approval of the Owner's Committee. Each Owner shall promptly provide all other Owners a copy of a notice of any default by or disagreement with a landowner, or notice of default by an Owner, under any Land Rights Document, as well as any communication with such landowner or any other relevant Owner related to the Land Rights Document or rights or obligations thereunder that would reasonably be expected to be material to the interest of the Owners. Taxes. Each Owner shall pay, when due, its Proportionate Share of all real and personal property taxes and assessments, general or special, levied against the Shared Facilities and/or operations pursuant to this Agreement, or required to be paid by the Owners pursuant to the Land Rights Documents, subject to such Owner's right to contest by appropriate legal proceedings the validity or applicability of any such taxes and assessments. Transfer Taxes, Sales and Use Taxes. In the event of a transfer or sale of all or part of an Owner's interests in the Shared Facilities, the non-transferring Owners shall have no obligation with respect to any resulting transfer taxes or sales and use taxes, and shall be held harmless against same by the transferring Owner (unless they are the purchaser or transferee of such interest in the Shared Facilities). Compliance with Law. Each Owner shall, at its sole cost and expense, promptly comply in all material respects with all Laws and with all covenants, conditions and restrictions in effect during the term of this Agreement or any part thereof regulating the use of the Shared Facilities, its Project and/or its exercise of its rights under the Land Rights Documents; provided however, that such Party shall have the right to contest by appropriate legal proceedings the validity or applicability of any such Laws. Conduct of Activities. Each Owner shall (a) conduct its operations and activities with respect to the Shared Facilities, its Project and the Land Use Documents in accordance with Good Utility Practices, and (b) keep its Project in good condition and repair, in good and efficient working order and in a safe condition. No Owner shall conduct its operations or activities, or use or permit the use of the lands burdened by the Shared Facility Lands Rights, or any part thereof, in any manner that will damage the such lands, or any part thereof. Except as otherwise set forth in this Agreement, each Owner's use of the Shared Facilities shall not in any way materially interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Owners of their respective in such Shared Facilities or other rights arising under this Agreement. No Owner shall use or permit the use of the Shared Facilities in any manner that would create waste or nuisance, or that would materially increase the premium, or materially jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy of any Owner relating to the Shared Facilities. No Owner shall act or fail to act in a manner that would interfere with any other Owner's ownership or use of the Shared Facilities, including but not limited to any such interference that would curtail or diminish another Owners ability to deliver the electrical output of its Project. Cooperation. Subject to Section 3.1(g), each Owner shall reasonably cooperate with the other Owner with respect to the interconnection, start-up and testing of their respective Projects, and in all other matters necessary for the Owners to realize their full use of the Shared Facilities and Shared Facilities Land Rights. Securing and Maintain Project Interconnection; Notice of Interconnection Agreement Defaults. Each Owner shall be responsible for securing and maintaining such rights as are necessary to interconnect such Owner's Project with the transmission and interconnection system of the Transmission Owner. No Liens on Shared Facilities. Except as provided in Article 9, no Owner shall create, permit or suffer to exist by, through or under such Owner any liens on the Shared Facilities, except for (a) liens for taxes that are not yet delinquent or are being contested in good faith by appropriate proceedings, and (b) mechanic's, materialmen's or other like liens that arise from the construction, reconstruction, ownership or operation of such Shared Facilities; provided that if any mechanics' liens or similar liens attached to the Shared Facilities, the Owner performing or contracting or causing the engagement of the holder of such attached lien shall, within thirty (30) days after it receives notice of the filing, either bond around such lien or establish appropriate reserves therefor, or otherwise remove such lien from such Shared Facilities pursuant to applicable Law. Damage or Destruction. In the event of any damage or destruction to, or other failure of all or any part of the Shared Facilities, the Operator shall take all commercially reasonable actions as may be necessary or appropriate to repair or replace the affected Shared Facilities or other facilities in order to restore the affected Shared Facilities or other facilities to substantially the same condition (or better) as before such damage or destruction (and any costs associated with such actions, after accounting for recoveries under any applicable insurance policies, will be shared by the Owners pro rata based on their Ownership Interest, as applicable). Condemnation or Damage Awards. Any condemnation or damage awards or other sums to which the Owners shall become entitled under the Land Rights Documents or with respect to the Shared Facilities shall be shared in proportion to their respective Ownership Interests, provided that if such sums are in reimbursement of or compensation for specific costs or damages incurred by the Owners in ratios different from that of their Ownership Interests, then such different ratios shall be used in apportionment of such sums among the Owners. INSURANCE Insurance for Shared Facilities. The Operator (or, if otherwise agreed by the Owners Committee, each Owner) shall procure at the earliest practicable time and thereafter maintain in effect at all times hereinafter provided insurance which it in good faith believes is consistent with Good Utility Practices for properties and facilities substantially similar to the Shared Facilities. Each Owner shall be named as an additional insured on (i) the property insurance required pursuant to Section 8.1(a) with respect to the Ownership Interest of each Owner, and (ii) the commercial general liability insurance required pursuant to Section 8.1(a) with respect to the indemnities given in this Agreement. A copy of all policies of insurance procured by the Operator or the other Owner, pursuant to Section 8.1(a) shall be provided to any Owner upon such Owner's written request. The Operator shall notify each Owner in writing of (i) the assertion of any claim for bodily injury or property damage in excess of one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) or greater related to the Shared Facilities promptly following the Operator's knowledge of any such assertion and (ii) the Operator's knowledge of the occurrence of an event likely, in the reasonable determination of the Operator, to result in the assertion of such a claim promptly following any such occurrence. If any loss, damage or impairment to the Shared Facilities occurs, the Operator shall apply the proceeds of any insurance policy with respect thereto to repair, replace or restore the Shared Facilities to their prior condition. The insurance policies and coverages required to be procured pursuant to this Article 8 shall be reviewed annually by the Owners Committee. Transfer of Interests; Liens Restrictions on Transfer. No Owner shall, directly or indirectly, sell, assign or otherwise transfer all or any of its Ownership Interest or other rights or interests in or to the Shared Facilities, or in, to or under this Agreement, without (i) assigning or transferring such interest in such Owner's Project, the Shared Facilities, this Agreement, and the Land Rights Documents together to the same assignee, such that the Owners' Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities is not separated in ownership from its rights and interests under this Agreement and the Land Rights Documents and such Owner's Project, and (ii) obtaining the prior written consent of the Owners Committee, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed by the Owners Committee, except that such consent shall not be required for a sale, assignment or transfer by an Owner (a "Transferring Party") in the following circumstances: if the purchaser, assignee or transferee is an entity with which the Transferring Party has consolidated or into which the Transferring Party has merged and such purchaser, assignee, lessee or assignee shall have agreed in writing for the benefit of the other Owners to unconditionally assume, on a recourse basis, the due and punctual performance and observance of all of the future obligations of such Transferring Party under this Agreement; provided that any non-transferring Owner may require as a condition of any such transfer such approvals from FERC or any other entity as may be required by Laws or contract (if any); the assignee or transferee of an Owner's Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities is the holder of any debt of such Transferring Party and the assignment or transfer by such Transferring Party is pursuant to the terms of a mortgage, trust, security agreement, indenture or other instrument of indebtedness to which the Transferring Party and such holder of debt (or such trustee) are parties, as security for bonds or other indebtedness of the Transferring Party, or the transferee is any party acquiring such interest through foreclosure or deed in lieu of foreclosure, or from the holder of the debt of the Transferring Party after the holder of the debt acquired such interest through foreclosure or deed in lieu of foreclosure; or in connection with the transfer of all or a portion of such Owner's right, title and interest in any Project served by the Shared Facilities and the Land Rights Documents, if the acquirer shall have agreed in writing for the benefit of the other Owner(s) to unconditionally assume, on a recourse basis, the due and punctual performance and observance of all of the future obligations of such Transferring Party under this Agreement and the Land Rights Documents and the assignment is permitted pursuant to the Land Rights Documents; provided that any non-assigning or non-transferring Owner may require as a condition of any such transfer such approvals from FERC or any other entity as may be required by Laws or contract (if any). The number of Owners Committee members shall remain unaffected by any such transfer, and the total number of members on the Owners Committee shall remain three (3), unless otherwise unanimously agreed by the Owners Committee members. Transfer Requirements. No sale, assignment or other transfer of any interest in the Shared Facilities (or in any part of the Shared Facilities) pursuant to Section 9.1 above, or that requires the consent of the other Owners Committee, may be made by any Owner unless simultaneously such Owner's rights in, to and under this Agreement and the Land Rights Documents that relate to such interest are similarly sold, assigned or transferred to the same Person or Persons, and such Person or Persons have assumed in writing all of the duties and obligations under this Agreement and the Land Rights Documents of the Owner making such sale, assignment or transfer that relate to such interest. Any such sale, assignment or transfer permitted pursuant to Section 9.1 above (i) shall relieve an Owner of any future obligation under this Agreement, provided that the transferee agrees in writing to assume all such obligations, and (ii) shall relieve an Owner of any past obligation under this Agreement only to the extent consented to in writing by the other Owner(s). No Owner may transfer all or part of its rights to use the Shared Facilities separately from its Ownership Interest or a transfer of an interest in a Project served by the Shared Facilities. Any attempted or purported sale, assignment or other transfer of any interest in the Shared Facilities or this Agreement made other than in accordance with this Article 9 either voluntarily or by operation of law shall be void and of no force or effect. Obligations Regarding Liens. Except for liens upon an Owner's Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities securing obligations owed by such Owner to a financing party, no Owner shall, directly or indirectly, create, incur, or permit to exist any lien on the Shared Facilities including but not limited to taxes (other than for taxes not yet due), judgments, construction work, repair and restoration, or materials furnished. In the event of a violation of this Section 9.3 that is not cured within thirty (30) days after the offending Owner receives notice of the recordation of such a lien, the other Owner(s) shall be entitled to remove or cause the removal of such liens or encumbrances and to be reimbursed by the offending Owner for all costs and expenses incurred in removing such liens or encumbrances. Succession as "Owner". Any permitted purchaser, assignee or transferee (other than a collateral assignee pursuant to a lien securing an obligation to a financing party prior to foreclosure thereon) shall be considered an "Owner" for purposes of this Agreement. DEFAULT AND REMEDIES Defaults. The occurrence and continuation of any of the following events shall constitute an event of default of an Owner under this Agreement (an "Event of Default"): Payment. A Owner fails to pay when due any amounts required to by paid by such Owner under this Agreement, and such failure to pay is not cured within ten (10) days following written notice from any other Owner or the Operator specifying the amount to be paid, provided that such period shall be extended for so long as the allegedly defaulting Owner is disputing in good faith such amount pursuant to the procedures set forth in Article 11. Bankruptcy. If an Owner files a petition or otherwise commences, or authorizes or acquiesces in the commencement of, a proceeding or cause under any bankruptcy, insolvency, receivership or similar law for the protection of creditors or suffers the filing of an involuntary bankruptcy petition or proceeding commenced against it, which in the case of an involuntary petition or proceeding remains undismissed and unstayed for one hundred twenty (120) days; Other Defaults. A Owner fails to cure (a) any breach of the covenants set forth in Section 7.7(a) or 7.1(d) by the earlier to occur of (i) fifteen (15) days following written notice from any other Owner specifying the nature of the failure to perform, or (ii) the date by which such breach is required to be cured to avoid an event of default under the applicable agreement covered by such Sections, or (b) any other unexcused and uncured failure to perform in any material respect any obligation under this Agreement, which failure to perform could reasonably be expected to materially and adversely affect another Owner's realization of the material benefits of this Agreement or the ability of either Owner to perform its material obligations under this Agreement, within thirty (30) days following written notice from any other Owner specifying the nature of the failure to perform, provided that such respect to clause (b), if the default is not reasonably capable of being cured within thirty (30) days, then the defaulting Owner may be allowed such longer period as the Owners mutually agree upon and as may be reasonably necessary under the circumstances to cure such failure so long as the defaulting Owner is pursuing a cure with reasonable diligence. Default by Operator. Operator fails to perform any of its obligations hereunder, and such failure is not cured within ten (10) days following written notice thereof from any Owner; provided that, that if such failure by Operator creates an Emergency Condition or materially interferes with an Owner's Undivided Use Interest in Shared Facilities, or operation of its Project, only such advance written notice, if any, as may be reasonably practicable under the circumstances shall be required, but if such advance notice is not provided, written notice thereof shall be provided promptly thereafter by Owner to Operator. Seizure of Property. Any substantial property of an Owner is subjected to any levy, seizure, assignment or sale for or by any creditor or Governmental Authority that materially affects that Owner's ability to perform under this Agreement. Merger, Consolidation without Assumption of Obligations. An Owner consolidates or amalgamates with, or merges with or into, or transfers all or substantially all of its assets to, another entity and, at the time of such consolidation, amalgamation, merger or transfer, the resulting, surviving or transferee entity fails to assume all the obligations of such Owner under this Agreement to which it or its predecessor was a party by operation of law or pursuant to an agreement reasonably satisfactory to the other Owners. Remedies upon Default. Remedies Upon Owner Default. If any Owner default is not cured within the applicable cure period (if any) provided in Section 10.1 by making or tendering the required payment or performance, each Owner not in default (a "Non-Defaulting Owner") shall have the right (i) to cure the default at the expense of the defaulting Owner, in which event the defaulting Owner shall reimburse the curing Owners all of the curing Owner's costs of cure within thirty (30) days of invoice, or curing Owners may offset such costs against any sums then or thereafter owed by the curing Owners to the defaulting Owner; (ii) to enforce specific performance; or (iii) to enforce any other remedy available to the Non-Defaulting Owner at law or in equity, subject to Section 10.2(a)(i) below and Article 12. In no event shall any Owner be entitled to terminate this Agreement on account of default by or the bankruptcy or insolvency of another Owner hereto. None of the bankruptcy or insolvency of an Owner, or default by an Owner under this Agreement shall be grounds for terminating this Agreement. Notwithstanding anything contained in this Agreement to the contrary, if an Owner's default under this Agreement creates a material interference with another a Non-Defaulting Owner's operations or maintenance of such Non-Defaulting Owner's Project, the Non-Defaulting Owner(s) shall have the right to any expedited remedies that may be available hereunder at law or in equity, including the right to cure such default as provided in Section 10.2(a), and the right to reimbursement of all reasonable costs actually incurred by such Non-Defaulting Owner in effecting such cure. Remedies Upon Operator Default. If Operator defaults pursuant to Section 10.1(d), any Owner may at its option access the Shared Facilities and perform (or cause to be performed) operation, maintenance, repair or other duties on behalf of Operator, and Operator shall reimburse such Owner's reasonable costs and expenses incurred by (or on behalf of) Owner promptly upon Operator's receipt of an invoice accompanied by documentation evidencing such costs and expenses and their reasonableness. In addition to the remedies provided in Section 10.2(a) and (b) above, if the defaulting Owner is Operator, a non-defaulting Owners shall have the right to appoint another Owner to serve as the Operator for purposes of this Agreement, and upon any such appointment and acceptance thereof by the Owner appointed to act as Operator, the defaulting Operator shall be removed as Operator; provided that such removal of the Operator shall not relieve the removed Operator of any liability hereunder for any acts or omissions as Operator prior to the effective time of such removal. The Owners and the defaulting Operator shall cooperate with each other in effecting such transition and provide all notices to third parties and take all other actions deemed necessary or advisable by any of them with respect to such change in status. No Waiver. If on any occasion an Owner does not insist upon the performance of any term, condition or provision of this Agreement, such forbearance will not operate or be construed as an acceptance of any variation in any term, condition or provision of this Agreement or relinquishment of any right under this Agreement. No waiver by an Owner of any right or of any default by the other Owners under this Agreement will be effective unless it is in writing and signed by the waiving Owner, and no waiver will operate or be construed as a waiver of any other or further right or as a waiver of any future default, whether of like or different character or nature. Interest on Late Payments. Any payment not made by a defaulting Owner when due and owing pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement may be advanced by any other Owner or Owners in its or their discretion and, if so advanced, shall be repayable to such other Owner(s) by the defaulting Owner, with interest at the Interest Rate, such interest to accrue on the amount due and on the accrued interest from (and including) the date such payment was due until paid in full together with such accrued interest. Remedies Cumulative. The remedies available pursuant to this Article 10 shall be in addition to and not in lieu of other remedies available to the non-defaulting Owner pursuant to this Agreement or at law or in equity, and the exercise of remedies pursuant to this Article 10 shall not release the defaulting Owner from any of its obligations under this Agreement Existing Liens Not Affected. No remedy or action taken pursuant to this Article 10 by a non-defaulting Owner in connection with a default by another Owner is intended to give rise to the creation of any lien, claim or encumbrance of any non-defaulting Owner that is prior to the lien, claim or encumbrance of any secured party under any mortgage, loan, credit agreement or other security agreement or instrument of indebtedness between such secured party and such defaulting Owner existing as of the occurrence of such default by such defaulting Owner, except to the extent permitted under such mortgage, loan, credit agreement, other security agreement or instrument of indebtedness. In the event of any dispute arising under this Agreement, including a dispute in which one Owner seeks to remove and replace the Operator, within five (5) days following the delivered date of a written request by an Owner, a senior executive each Owner shall meet, negotiate and attempt in good faith to resolve the dispute quickly, informally and inexpensively.
